       \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"the-9th-generation-ipad-is-just-19999\"\u003eThe 9th Generation iPad is just $199.99\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe iPad of the hour is the \u003ca href=\"https://zdcs.link/9wGknb?pageview_type=Standard\u0026amp;template=Deals\u0026amp;module=content-body\u0026amp;element=offer\u0026amp;item=text-link\u0026amp;element_label=9th%20Generation%20iPad%20Wi-Fi%2064GB\u0026amp;short_url=9wGknb\u0026amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Flifehacker.com%2Ftech%2Fipads-deals-will-arrive-before-christmas\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"open in a new window\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e9th Generation iPad Wi-Fi 64GB\u003c/a\u003e from 2021, which, \u003ca href=\"https://lifehacker.com/tech/amazon-deal-of-the-day-9th-generation-ipad\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esince August\u003c/a\u003e, has dropped to an impressive \u003cstrong\u003e$199.99\u003c/strong\u003e (originally $329.99). This iPad is already sold out at most reputable retailers since it\u0026#39;s the cheapest iPad you can get at the moment, but as of the time of this writing, Target still has them in space gray. If Target is out of stock by the time you read this, \u003ca href=\"https://zdcs.link/z6bGV3?pageview_type=Standard\u0026amp;template=Deals\u0026amp;module=content-body\u0026amp;element=offer\u0026amp;item=text-link\u0026amp;element_label=Walmart%20is%20the%20next%20best%20place%20to%20find%20them\u0026amp;short_url=z6bGV3\u0026amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Flifehacker.com%2Ftech%2Fipads-deals-will-arrive-before-christmas\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"open in a new window\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eWalmart is the next best place to find them\u003c/a\u003e, but they\u0026#39;re $249. You can read more about this iPad in \u003ca href=\"https://www.pcmag.com/reviews/apple-ipad-2021\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"open in a new window\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003ePCMag\u0026#39;s review\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"the-10th-generation-ipad-is-70-off\"\u003eThe 10th Generation iPad is $70 off\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe next best iPad deal available is the newer \u003ca href=\"https://zdcs.link/QrpDrE?pageview_type=Standard\u0026amp;template=Deals\u0026amp;module=content-body\u0026amp;element=offer\u0026amp;item=text-link\u0026amp;element_label=10th-generation%20iPad%20Wi-Fi%2064GB\u0026amp;short_url=QrpDrE\u0026amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Flifehacker.com%2Ftech%2Fipads-deals-will-arrive-before-christmas\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"open in a new window\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e10th-generation iPad Wi-Fi 64GB\u003c/a\u003e, available for \u003cstrong\u003e$279.99\u003c/strong\u003e (originally $349.99). When the 10th-generation iPad was released in the winter of 2022, it was considered the “best tablet for most people,” according to \u003ca href=\"https://www.pcmag.com/reviews/apple-ipad-2022\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"open in a new window\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e\u003cu\u003ePCMag’s “excellent” review\u003c/u\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. It measures 9.79 by 7.07 by 0.28 inches, it includes the A14 Bionic chip, a 10.9-inch liquid retina display, 64GB of storage, a 12MP front and back camera, Touch ID, and a battery that Apple promises will last all day. You can read more about the differences between the \u003ca href=\"https://lifehacker.com/tech/which-is-better-ipad-9-or-ipad-10\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e9th vs 10th generation iPads here\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"the-latest-ipad-air-is-100-off\"\u003eThe latest iPad Air is $100 off\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026#39;re looking for the latest iPad Air, the M2 iPad Air \u003ca href=\"https://lifehacker.com/tech/best-preorder-deals-on-11th-generation-ipads\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ecame out this summer\u003c/a\u003e, and the \u003ca href=\"https://zdcs.link/QVD1M1?pageview_type=Standard\u0026amp;template=Deals\u0026amp;module=content-body\u0026amp;element=offer\u0026amp;item=text-link\u0026amp;element_label=11-inch%20128GB%20iPad%20Air\u0026amp;short_url=QVD1M1\u0026amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Flifehacker.com%2Ftech%2Fipads-deals-will-arrive-before-christmas\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"open in a new window\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e11-inch 128GB iPad Air\u003c/a\u003e is on sale for \u003cstrong\u003e$499\u003c/strong\u003e (originally $599). Though not a huge discount, it\u0026#39;s still impressive given it came out a few months ago. The new M2 chip gives it better performance than the older models. Some new features on the iPad Air include split-view screens, subject lift, and live text features. You can read more about the M2 iPad Air from \u003ca href=\"https://www.pcmag.com/reviews/apple-ipad-air-2024\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"open in a new window\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003e\u003cu\u003ePCMag\u0026#39;s \u0026#34;excellent\u0026#34; review\u003c/u\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eKeep in mind this iPad Air is a premium tablet that may be overkill for most people. As Lifehacker\u0026#39;s tech editor Jake Peterson said, \u0026#34;\u003ca href=\"https://lifehacker.com/tech/apple-ipad-sale-prime-day\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cu\u003eThey\u0026#39;re overbuilt\u003c/u\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u0026#34; But if you want the best, that\u0026#39;s the one.\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n                        \u003cdiv\u003e\n                \u003cdiv\u003e\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://lifehacker.com/imagery/authors/01HF2FBG3NFZ3WZWX5Q6M3PDM4/image.fill.size_150x150.v1704301325.png\" alt=\"Daniel Oropeza caricature \" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\"/\u003e\n                                            \u003c/p\u003e\n                \u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\n                \u003cp\u003eDaniel Oropeza\u003c/p\u003e\n                                    \u003cp\u003eStaff Writer\u003c/p\u003e\n                                \u003cdiv\u003e\n                             